  "title": "Receptionist - [ST]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Serve as the first point of contact for all visitors, ensuring a warm, professional, and polished reception experience</p></li><li><p>Welcome and attend to VIP guests, senior executives, and external stakeholders with discretion and confidence</p></li><li><p>Manage meeting room bookings, guest registrations, and coordination of refreshments and hospitality arrangements</p></li><li><p>Handle incoming calls, emails, and general enquiries in a courteous and professional manner</p></li><li><p>Support front desk administration, including visitor passes, courier handling, and document coordination</p></li><li><p>Liaise with internal teams to ensure seamless guest arrivals, meetings, and departures</p></li><li><p>Maintain a presentable reception area that reflects the company’s corporate image and standards</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prior experience as a Receptionist or in premium customer service roles</p></li><li><p>Strong preference for candidates with backgrounds in <strong>cabin crew, VIP airport lounges, luxury hospitality, or high-end customer service environments</strong></p></li><li><p>Confident, well-groomed, and professionally presented, with strong interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Calm, discreet, and composed when handling VIPs and sensitive situations</p></li><li><p>Service-oriented mindset with attention to detail and strong organisational skills</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a corporate, fast-paced MNC environment<br /></p><p>We appreciate your interest and look forward to reviewing your application. Due to high application volume, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted — thank you for your understanding!</p><p></p><p>WeCruit Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel: Tan Soon Hock (Steven) | Registration No. R1109889</p></li></ul>",
